│ present in the VMap because VMap only contains mappings for Instructions and other non-constant Values that were cloned during loop peeling. Constants    │
│ don't need to be cloned since they are immutable and can be shared. However, the code at line 1217 assumes that VMap.lookup(E) will always return a valid │
│ non-null value.\n\nThe fix is to check if E is a Constant, and if so, use E directly instead of looking it up in VMap, since constants don't need         │
│ mapping.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n   + Line 1217 in llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/LoopPeel.cpp should be modified to handle the case where E is a       │
│ Constant by using E directly, or to use VMap.lookup(E) only when E is not a Constant.\n\n5. Conclusion: The fix ensures that when replacing uses of exit  │
│ PHI nodes during last-iteration peeling, constant values are used directly instead of attempting to look them up in the value map (which would return     │
│ null). This prevents the assertion failure and allows the peeling transformation to complete successfully."})                                             │
